  "prompt": "What is debt deflation?",
  "response": "Debt deflation is an economic concept where declining asset prices and increased real value of debt lead to a vicious economic cycle. Here are key characteristics:\n\n1. Definition:\n- A situation where falling prices increase the real burden of debt\n- Occurs when the value of debt remains constant while asset values and income decline\n\n2. Process:\n- Asset prices fall\n- Value of debt remains the same\n- Debt becomes proportionally more expensive\n- Borrowers struggle to repay loans\n- Leads to reduced spending and investment\n\n3. Economic consequences:\n- Decreased consumer spending\n- Reduced business investment\n- Higher unemployment\n- Potential economic recession or depression\n\n4. Typical sequence:\n- Asset prices drop\n- Debt becomes relatively more expensive\n- Borrowers sell assets to repay debt\n- Further asset price decline\n- Reduced economic activity\n\n5. Historical example:\n- Great Depression of 1929-1933\n- Debt deflation was a significant factor in economic contraction\n\n6. Potential mitigation strategies:\n- Monetary policy interventions\n- Debt restructuring\n- Government stimulus\n- Central bank support\n\nDebt deflation is a complex economic phenomenon that can significantly impact financial systems and economic growth.",
